Youtube Video ANALYSIS

Dataset¶

Dataset (Structured): https://www.kaggle.com/mfekadu/youtube-kaggle/data
Dataset (Unstructured): https://drive.google.com/file/d/0ByJLBTmJojjzR2x0MzVpc2Z6enM/view

Dataset Description¶

Column 1: Video id of 11 characters.

Column 2: uploader of the video

Column 3: Interval between the day of establishment of Youtube and the date of uploading of the video.

Column 4: Category of the video.

Column 5: Length of the video.

Column 6: Number of views for the video.

Column 7: Rating on the video.

Column 8: Number of ratings given for the video

Column 9: Number of comments done on the videos.

Column 10: Related video ids with the uploaded video.

import pandas as pd

Analysis of Data using NEO4j UnStructured¶

1. Getting 25 nodes¶

MATCH p=()-->() RETURN p LIMIT 25

2. Getting a Node by particular ID¶

MATCH p=(n)-[k:SIMILAR_TO]->(f) WHERE n.videoid = 'QuRYeRnAuXM' RETURN p LIMIT 25

3. Getting Node by Category and Particular Direction¶

MATCH p=(n)-[k:SIMILAR_TO]->(f) WHERE n.videoid = 'QuRYeRnAuXM'and (n)-->(f) RETURN p

4.Displaying Categories¶

MATCH p=(n)-[k:SIMILAR_TO]->(f) WHERE n.category= 'Entertainment' RETURN p

Analysis of Data using Hadoop-MapReduce¶

  1. Top 5 categories with maximum number of videos uploaded. (Top n Pattern)
  2. Find the top 5 rated videos on YouTube.
  3. Here videos are arranged by their length.
  4. Arranged Videos by Ratings.
  5. Distinct pattern to get distinct categories (Distinct Patter)
  6. Group Categories and sort by videoIDS (Secondary Sort Pattern)
